## The DoC's Office
The DoC has a number of consoles in their office that help them do the various functions of their job.

## Station Administration
  <Box>
    <GuideEntityEmbed Entity="ComputerTabletopStationAdminBankATMMedical" Caption="Station Administration "
  </Box>
[color=RoyalBlue]The Station Administration console[/color] is your station [color=Gold]bank account[/color]. You are generally allowed to use it as you see fit, as long as you do so reasonably. The definition of "reasonable" is intentionally vague, but part of getting whitelisted is the admins and community in general trusting your judgement and roleplay sense. So [color=Green]trust yourself[/color]; if you think an expense is reasonable, it probably is.

To withdraw, put an amount to withdraw, pick the reason closest to what you're withdrawing it for, give a short description of what you're getting it for, and click Withdraw. The admins will check these sometimes, but as long as you're doing something reasonable there won't be an issue. Taking 10,000 spesos for "Buying food" is [color=LightSeaGreen]fine[/color], taking 1,000,000 spesos for "funny clown show" probably [color=Red]isn't[/color].

To deposit, insert spesos just like you would for an ATM, and fill out the deposit fields just like you would the withdrawal fields. 

## Announcement Console
  <Box>
    <GuideEntityEmbed Entity="ComputerTabletopComms" Caption="Announcement Console"
  </Box>
[color=RoyalBlue]The Announcement Console[/color] is used to send messages to the whole sector. Generally, you just enter your announcement in the field and click the "announce" button. The drop-down menu with colors is there to set the [color=Red]sector alert level[/color], you should not be editing that unless instructed to by the SR or Sheriff.

## MD shuttle console
  <Box>
    <GuideEntityEmbed Entity="ComputerTabletopShuttle" Caption="MD shuttle console"
  </Box>
You also have a shuttle console for the MD itself. This works like a normal shuttle console, where you can undock ships, scan the sector, and keep an eye out for ship-based trouble. If you're coordinating medical response, you can use this to find out how far away different ships are to the alert using the map tab.

## Spare Consoles
  <Box>
    <GuideEntityEmbed Entity="ComputerTabletopShuttle" Caption="MD shuttle console"
    <GuideEntityEmbed Entity="ComputerTabletopComms" Caption="Announcement Console"
  </Box>
By default, you will spawn in with flatpacks for the Station Administration console and Announcement Console. These are also found in the DoC's office, but the ones you spawn in with can be brought aboard a ship that you buy and used to access these functions while away from MD. It's relatively common for DoCs to purchase a large ship to use as a mobile hospital, 

and these two consoles cover what you might need to not use MD at all.

## Your PDA
  <Box>
    <GuideEntityEmbed Entity="DocPDA" Caption="MD shuttle console"
  </Box>
Your PDA has two functions not available to normal contractors.

The first is the [color=Gold]Spesoflow Lite app[/color]. This app lets you track your [color=LightGoldenRodYellow]budget[/color], showing you where money is coming in and being spent. Your budget will mostly come from [color=Green]Vaults[/color], [color=Red]Taxes[/color], and [color=Cyan]Medical Bounties[/color].

The second is Command Bounties. In the normal Bounty app, there's a second Command tab that is only available to Command personnel. You can use this to put up bounties for anything you need, and given the smaller number of people posting there, it'll remain more visible through the round. Remember to take down any bounties you put up before you cryo, though.

